Data Archive for NASA Black Marble Data
VNP46A1 : https://ladsweb.modaps.eosdis.nasa.gov/archive/allData/5000/VNP46A1/
VNP46A2 : https://ladsweb.modaps.eosdis.nasa.gov/archive/allData/5000/VNP46A2/
VNP46A3: https://ladsweb.modaps.eosdis.nasa.gov/archive/allData/5000/VNP46A3/
VNP46A4: https://ladsweb.modaps.eosdis.nasa.gov/archive/allData/5000/VNP46A4/
To download data for selected region we can either use bounding box feature offer on the website.
Or we can select the tile based on the grid reference below 

![GRIDREFERENCE!](https://github.com/jyotibiswas1708/MB1/issues/1#issuecomment-1531556380)

  
Fig 1: The Suomi-NPP VIIRS linear latitude/longitude (or geographic) grid consists of 460 non-overlapping Land tiles which measure approximately 10°×10° region.
The filenames follow a naming convention which gives useful information regarding the specific product. For example, the filename VNP46A1.A2015001.h08v05.001.2017012234657.h5 indicates: 
(1) VNP46A1: Product Short Name; 
(2) A2015001: Julian Date of Acquisition (A-YYYYDDD);
(3) h08v05: Tile Identifier (horizontalXXverticalYY);
(4) .001: Collection Version;
(5) .2017012234657: Julian Date of Production (YYYYDDDHHMMSS); 
(6) .h5: Data Format (HDF5).
Tool to convert the HDF file to GeoTiff : https://blackmarble.gsfc.nasa.gov/Tools.html
